WEBVTT

00:01.164 --> 00:03.003
Spence Westmore, you're under arrest

00:03.054 --> 00:05.464
- for the murder of Peri Westmore.
- No, no, he didn't do it!

00:05.515 --> 00:08.999
Maybe Peri told the cult about the
man who drugged and raped her.

00:09.050 --> 00:10.609
I think he's the killer.

00:10.660 --> 00:12.907
There is a video of Peri

00:12.958 --> 00:14.418
being interviewed by The Circle.

00:14.469 --> 00:17.639
If we had it, we can prove
Spence is innocent.

00:17.873 --> 00:18.697
I can't.

00:18.748 --> 00:19.761
The Circle is gone?

00:19.812 --> 00:22.538
Zoila went next door,
and the place was cleaned out.

00:23.002 --> 00:24.752
Oh, my God.
Is that a tunnel?

00:24.803 --> 00:25.768
You coming with me?

00:25.819 --> 00:27.776
- I'm Fiona.
- I thought you were... in Italy.

00:27.827 --> 00:29.466
You must be Zoila, my maid.

00:29.517 --> 00:30.803
I know you're my mother now.

00:30.854 --> 00:32.186
I can't be that for you.

00:32.237 --> 00:34.358
They're casting the movie
based on Marisol's book.

00:34.409 --> 00:35.653
I got a callback.

00:35.704 --> 00:36.695
You did?

00:36.746 --> 00:38.739
Peter.
Husband number three.

00:38.790 --> 00:40.790
I happen to think
you're sexy as hell.

00:40.841 --> 00:42.685
"I didn't know what kind
of flowers you liked,

00:42.736 --> 00:44.198
so I got them all."

00:44.628 --> 00:45.586
Peter."

00:45.637 --> 00:46.762
A little birdie told me

00:46.813 --> 00:49.451
that Marisol got back together
with Jesse.

00:49.502 --> 00:51.958
You were right.
Marisol's seeing her ex again.

00:52.009 --> 00:54.100
I really screwed things up
royally, huh?

00:54.151 --> 00:56.374
I didn't realize you were
so taken with Peter.

00:56.425 --> 00:58.834
Neither did I...
until he was gone.

00:58.885 --> 01:00.285
I'm not usually like this.

01:00.336 --> 01:01.884
It's just Peter.

01:01.935 --> 01:03.970
I never meant to cheat on him.

01:04.021 --> 01:05.498
What happened to you...

01:05.550 --> 01:06.631
that's rape.

01:06.682 --> 01:07.710
Who was it?

01:07.761 --> 01:09.655
Hugh Metzger...
the director.

01:09.706 --> 01:10.789
Mr. Metzger?

01:10.840 --> 01:11.809
Come on in.

01:11.859 --> 01:12.854
I'm leaving you.

01:12.904 --> 01:14.884
Evelyn, we were meant to be together.

01:15.220 --> 01:16.724
Oh! Dear God.

01:16.774 --> 01:18.945
Evelyn is jealous of me and Gail.

01:18.996 --> 01:20.428
You told me your marriage was over.

01:20.479 --> 01:22.182
I'm sorry.
I can't do this.

01:22.233 --> 01:24.074
I decided to give Evelyn her divorce.

01:24.125 --> 01:27.415
Gail, I am madly in love with you.

01:30.247 --> 01:31.520
Good morning, Evelyn...

01:31.570 --> 01:34.722
and attorney whose name
I will never learn.

01:34.772 --> 01:37.371
Shall we begin
the divorce negotiations?

01:37.421 --> 01:39.129
Will your attorney be joining us?

01:39.179 --> 01:40.864
No, no.
I didn't invite him.

01:40.914 --> 01:45.390
I'm certain we can divide
the assets fairly and amicably.

01:45.440 --> 01:47.625
We'll see how amicable you're feeling

01:47.675 --> 01:50.053
after you have read
my list of demands.

01:52.862 --> 01:55.130
The penthouse in Manhattan.

01:55.180 --> 01:57.129
I spent a great deal of effort
renovating that apart...

01:57.179 --> 01:58.506
It's yours.

01:58.928 --> 02:01.974
Our yacht,<i> The Lady Evelyn...</i>
yours again.

02:02.024 --> 02:03.635
In fact, this all seems acceptable.

02:03.685 --> 02:04.904
Agreed.

02:05.498 --> 02:06.538
Agreed. Agreed.

02:06.588 --> 02:10.857
I know it's not on the list,
but I also want the Manet.

02:10.907 --> 02:13.778
The Manet or the Monet?

02:14.042 --> 02:15.246
Both.

02:15.457 --> 02:16.718
Agreed.

02:16.768 --> 02:18.089
What the hell are you doing?

02:18.139 --> 02:21.026
She means, "Thank you." Yeah.

02:21.604 --> 02:23.886
I'll have the final documents
drawn up immediately.

02:23.936 --> 02:25.002
Wonderful.

02:25.052 --> 02:26.169
See?

02:26.606 --> 02:27.804
Amicable.

02:34.335 --> 02:37.258
Adrian, you have been fighting
this divorce for months,

02:37.308 --> 02:38.707
and suddenly you're just giving up?

02:38.757 --> 02:40.394
It's time for me to move on,

02:40.444 --> 02:43.056
just as you moved on
with Reverend Hamilton.

02:43.584 --> 02:44.502
Yes.

02:44.552 --> 02:47.157
Yes, we are very happy,
but I don't understand.

02:47.207 --> 02:48.256
What turned you around?

02:48.306 --> 02:50.521
Evelyn!
Oh, dear.

02:50.571 --> 02:52.718
This must be
a little bit awkward for you.

02:52.768 --> 02:55.671
Awkward?
Why would it be awkward?

02:55.721 --> 02:57.404
I haven't had the chance
to give her the news.

02:57.454 --> 02:59.509
Oh, let me tell her.

03:00.423 --> 03:02.774
Adrian and I are engaged!

03:03.752 --> 03:06.611
Is that the Powell Family
blood diamond?

03:07.910 --> 03:09.668
Adrian, this is insane.

03:09.718 --> 03:12.567
I assumed you'd be happy.
You're finally free of me.

03:12.617 --> 03:15.763
That's exactly what you want,
isn't it?

