03:28.851 --> 03:32.253
Rosie, what do you know
about Peri's killer?

03:32.303 --> 03:33.805
I think he's the same man

03:33.855 --> 03:37.185
who drugged Peri
and raped her years ago...

03:37.404 --> 03:39.191
Tucker's real father.

03:39.339 --> 03:40.363
I can't say who,

03:40.413 --> 03:43.205
but I know someone who's had
a very similar experience,

03:43.255 --> 03:46.537
and the man who assaulted her
was Hugh Metzger.

03:46.587 --> 03:47.838
Get out.

03:47.888 --> 03:49.727
Wait. The jerk
Who's directing your movie?

03:49.777 --> 03:51.559
Do you think he could have
killed Peri?

03:51.609 --> 03:56.144
Miss Shannon said Peri's rapist
was a big shot in the movie industry.

03:56.194 --> 03:57.690
<i>Ay, dios mío.</i>

03:57.740 --> 03:59.960
Danni had a callback with him
last night.

04:02.736 --> 04:04.643
<i>Contesta.</i>
Danni, pick up. Pick up.

04:04.693 --> 04:06.605
- <i>Hello?</i>
- Daniela.

04:06.655 --> 04:07.636
Are you okay?

04:07.686 --> 04:08.744
Yeah, I'm fine.
What's wrong?

04:08.794 --> 04:10.025
Oh, thank God.

04:10.075 --> 04:13.346
Listen to me...
stay away from Hugh Metzger.

04:13.396 --> 04:14.320
What?

04:14.370 --> 04:17.156
He drugs and rapes women,
and he could be a killer, Danni.

04:17.207 --> 04:18.861
Unbelievable!

04:18.911 --> 04:21.752
You're making up these crazy lies
because you're jealous of me.

04:21.802 --> 04:24.275
- I'm protecting you from a rapist.
- Please.

04:24.325 --> 04:26.901
He was super nice to me
at the callback last night.

04:26.951 --> 04:29.844
Well, o-okay. Maybe he's trying
to get you to trust him.

04:29.894 --> 04:31.119
But stay away from him.

04:31.169 --> 04:32.916
And do not drink
anything he gives you.

04:32.966 --> 04:34.752
Promise me, Danni, please.

04:36.221 --> 04:37.460
I promise.

04:37.510 --> 04:39.536
Now I got to go.
<i>Adios.</i>

04:40.216 --> 04:41.455
Who was that?

04:42.160 --> 04:44.218
Oh, just my cousin.

04:45.491 --> 04:47.082
Anyway, let's get back to work.

04:47.132 --> 04:48.159
You know, actually,

04:48.209 --> 04:49.721
I thought we'd take
a little bit of a break,

04:49.771 --> 04:51.860
maybe have a little wine.

04:52.681 --> 04:56.590
Oh, but shouldn't we keep rehearsing
for my big screen test?

04:56.640 --> 04:58.813
Come on.
You've got to loosen up.

04:59.211 --> 05:00.937
You do want the part, don't you?

05:05.346 --> 05:08.021
Genevieve Delatour
for Dr. Selevan.

05:08.071 --> 05:09.208
I'm a bit early.

05:09.258 --> 05:11.287
Oh, may I offer you a beverage
while you wait?

05:11.337 --> 05:13.027
We have sparkling water, champagne.

05:13.077 --> 05:14.373
Champagne?

05:14.423 --> 05:17.000
Oh, I'm so happy
I changed therapists.

05:17.050 --> 05:18.644
Yes, please.

05:21.587 --> 05:25.136
I always get here early
just for the bubbly.

05:25.186 --> 05:26.870
Got to love Beverly Hills.

05:26.920 --> 05:29.951
My waxer offers
complimentary Vicodin.

05:32.045 --> 05:33.811
So, what are you in for?

05:34.925 --> 05:37.044
I recently discovered, uh,

05:37.094 --> 05:40.473
some troubling things
about an incident in my past.

05:40.999 --> 05:42.670
You?
Breakup...

05:43.350 --> 05:44.828
two years ago.

05:45.257 --> 05:48.921
Letting go of relationships is...
It's not my strong suit.

05:48.971 --> 05:51.239
I've been holding onto mine for 20.

05:51.289 --> 05:55.124
Ohh. I love meeting somebody
who's more messed up than me.

05:56.484 --> 05:58.876
Oh, you should probably
leave the bottle.

05:58.926 --> 06:00.066
Oh.

06:00.728 --> 06:01.869
Cheers.

06:05.821 --> 06:07.563
Maids by Marisol.

06:08.399 --> 06:10.956
Yes. Peter. Hello.

06:11.294 --> 06:12.354
Give me the phone.

06:12.404 --> 06:14.167
No. You know I've
been trying to talk to him.

06:14.217 --> 06:15.866
Marisol, you don't under...
Just give me the phone.

06:15.916 --> 06:20.361
Hi. Peter, I have been missing
you like crazy...

06:21.686 --> 06:24.444
Oh. Hi, sir.

06:24.928 --> 06:27.150
Yes, we can find you a maid.

06:27.541 --> 06:29.940
How's Wednesday at 2:00?

06:30.572 --> 06:31.749
Great.

06:33.277 --> 06:35.145
- Wrong Peter?
- Shut up.

06:35.195 --> 06:36.655
I'm gonna go out on a limb

06:36.705 --> 06:39.071
and say you're still not over
your breakup?

06:39.121 --> 06:42.122
What breakup?
Peter has just disappeared.

06:42.172 --> 06:44.104
It's the best relationship
I've ever had,

06:44.154 --> 06:47.070
and I never even got the chance
to say I'm sorry...

06:47.290 --> 06:48.295
or goodbye.

06:48.345 --> 06:50.793
Well, why don't you stop
moping around here then

06:50.843 --> 06:52.777
and go out and find yourself
some closure, already?

06:52.827 --> 06:56.026
God, I envy you, Evelyn.
You seem completely over Adrian.

06:56.076 --> 06:57.229
Ohh!

06:57.279 --> 06:59.948
- Ah, you don't know yet.
- What?

07:00.914 --> 07:04.698
Adrian is marrying...

07:04.748 --> 07:05.718
Gail Fleming.

07:05.768 --> 07:07.357
- What?!
- I don't understand it.

07:07.407 --> 07:08.747
He has always despised her,

07:08.797 --> 07:11.413
and yet they're having
an engagement party

07:11.788 --> 07:14.122
at the mansion tomorrow.

07:14.451 --> 07:16.332
And you're my plus one, by the way.

07:16.382 --> 07:18.376
They invited <i> you?</i>

07:18.426 --> 07:19.551
Seems kind of aggressive.

07:19.601 --> 07:21.238
It's like he's going out of his way

07:21.288 --> 07:22.698
to rub my nose in it.

07:22.748 --> 07:25.071
Oh, maybe he's just trying
to make you jealous.

07:26.158 --> 07:27.894
Oh, my God.

07:28.754 --> 07:29.919
He doesn't want to marry Gail.

07:29.969 --> 07:32.262
He wants me to break them up
and come running back to him.

07:32.699 --> 07:34.298
Sounds like Adrian is playing

07:34.348 --> 07:36.381
a very high-stakes
game of chicken.

07:36.431 --> 07:39.560
If <i> that's</i> what he wants...

07:40.271 --> 07:43.770
then chicken we shall play.

07:44.694 --> 07:45.686
Here it is...

07:45.736 --> 07:47.180
the guest list
from the night of Peri's party.

07:47.230 --> 07:49.548
Thank God you saved this.

07:49.712 --> 07:51.455
What are all the sad faces?

07:51.505 --> 07:53.747
Peri wanted me to keep track of
anyone who didn't bring a gift

07:53.797 --> 07:55.634
so she knew who to publicly shame.

07:57.588 --> 07:59.557
There's his name...
Hugh Metzger.

07:59.607 --> 08:00.766
He <i> was</i> at the party.

08:00.816 --> 08:02.676
Which means
he could have murdered Peri.

08:02.726 --> 08:04.601
I told you.

08:06.021 --> 08:07.862
I'm gonna get Spence out of jail.

08:07.912 --> 08:09.529
Police! Step back!

08:16.148 --> 08:17.254
I got this.

08:17.304 --> 08:19.141
Check in the back.
You two, upstairs. Go.

08:19.191 --> 08:20.730
Detective, what's going on?

08:20.780 --> 08:23.434
I'm gonna ask you this once.
Where is Spence?

08:23.484 --> 08:25.313
I don't understand.
He's not at the prison?

08:25.363 --> 08:27.515
No. He escaped
with another inmate.

08:27.906 --> 08:29.355
Listen, if you're harboring him
here...

08:29.405 --> 08:30.792
I'm not. I swear.

08:30.842 --> 08:32.052
We didn't even know he was missing.

08:32.102 --> 08:33.991
- Is all this really necessary?
- Yes.

08:34.042 --> 08:36.289
Spence Westmore
is an escaped murderer.

08:36.339 --> 08:37.690
We have orders.

08:37.740 --> 08:40.953
Now, if he resists capture,
we will shoot to kill.

08:46.912 --> 08:50.246
I understand why Peter wouldn't
talk to me after what I did.

08:50.296 --> 08:53.187
You didn't do anything.
You were violated.

08:53.237 --> 08:54.765
And Peter was an a-hole

08:54.815 --> 08:56.902
for not even bothering
to find out what happened.

08:56.952 --> 08:59.595
You're right.
Thank you, Lori.

08:59.645 --> 09:03.062
Just reminds me how happy
I am that I'm not into men.

09:03.112 --> 09:04.550
Oh.

09:04.600 --> 09:05.941
You're a lesbian.

09:07.083 --> 09:08.705
Do you enjoy it?

09:08.755 --> 09:10.127
I do.

09:10.177 --> 09:11.898
No male egos.

09:11.948 --> 09:14.696
You don't have to watch
stupid things on TV.

09:14.747 --> 09:17.157
And you end up
with twice the wardrobe.

09:17.207 --> 09:20.959
Oh, well, when you put it like that,
I get the appeal.

09:21.009 --> 09:22.782
Dr. Selevan
is ready for you.

09:22.833 --> 09:26.159
Uh, actually,
I don't need my appointment.

09:26.209 --> 09:28.763
I've just had
The best therapy of my life.

09:29.715 --> 09:30.876
Aww.

09:34.415 --> 09:35.477
Oh, hey, Danni.

09:35.527 --> 09:39.233
Carmen, something bad happened
with Hugh Metzger.

09:39.283 --> 09:40.574
Where are you?

09:42.165 --> 09:44.995
Oh, my God.
Danni, are you okay?

09:45.046 --> 09:47.032
Did he touch you?
You can tell me.

09:47.083 --> 09:48.584
I'll kill him, but you can tell me.

09:48.634 --> 09:50.625
I'm fine, but Hugh's not.

09:50.938 --> 09:52.702
Oh, my God.

09:52.752 --> 09:55.332
- What happened?
- You told me he drugged women,

09:55.382 --> 09:57.902
so I switched our glasses
when he wasn't looking.

09:57.952 --> 09:59.451
Is he dead?

10:00.030 --> 10:02.107
Unfortunately, no.

10:02.530 --> 10:03.878
You did the right thing.

10:03.928 --> 10:06.678
If you hadn't warned me,
he would've done that to me,

10:06.728 --> 10:08.256
- and then...
- Shh. Shh. Shh.

10:08.307 --> 10:10.381
No. You're safe now.
It's okay.

10:10.431 --> 10:11.763
Should we call the police?

10:11.813 --> 10:14.754
No. No. The police are idiots.
They always screw up.

10:14.804 --> 10:16.906
Spence is in jail
while this guy goes free.

10:16.956 --> 10:18.142
No, no, no.

10:18.609 --> 10:19.787
I have an idea.

10:21.070 --> 10:22.637
Okay, the house is all clear,

10:22.687 --> 10:24.421
but Spence may try to make contact.

10:24.472 --> 10:26.875
Spence didn't kill Peri.

10:27.282 --> 10:28.778
But I know who did.

10:28.864 --> 10:30.065
Really?

10:30.115 --> 10:32.604
It was Hugh Metzger, the director.

10:32.654 --> 10:35.201
He drugged Peri and raped her.

10:36.561 --> 10:37.685
What?

10:38.651 --> 10:40.739
Over the years, I have heard rumors

10:40.789 --> 10:43.159
about Mr. Metzger
taking advantage of women.

10:43.209 --> 10:44.708
So, you believe me?

10:44.903 --> 10:49.102
Look, Rosie, even if he is a rapist,
it doesn't mean he's a murderer.

10:49.152 --> 10:52.176
Please.
Spence didn't do this.

10:52.254 --> 10:54.570
Then why is he on the run?

